<span id="freeTextContainer16762120718888437438">I&apos;ll be honest I didn&apos;t totally finish the book before giving up. I hear Vance on NPR and the story caught my attention. Yet, what I thought would be a better analysis of American economics and poverty proved to be very different. <br/><br/>It&apos;s one of those conservative love stories of &quot; I got my shit together so everyone can&quot;. While I respect the struggle Vance had, I also believe it&apos;s a very naive picture of what is going on. It explains why people FEEL a way. It does not explain the systemic issues th</span>
  <span id="freeText16762120718888437438" style="display:none">I'll be honest I didn't totally finish the book before giving up. I hear Vance on NPR and the story caught my attention. Yet, what I thought would be a better analysis of American economics and poverty proved to be very different. <br /><br />It's one of those conservative love stories of " I got my shit together so everyone can". While I respect the struggle Vance had, I also believe it's a very naive picture of what is going on. It explains why people FEEL a way. It does not explain the systemic issues that are also at play. <br /><br />Skip it if you want anything profound. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16762120718888437438" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

